  <discussion>Plants of Amaranthus australis, a herbaceous annual, can be amazingly tall, with a
        single hollow main stem, up to 9 m, and the stem base can reach 30 cm in diameter. Large
        plants may somewhat resemble young trees of Taxodium distichum var. imbricarium,
        pondcypress.</discussion>
